(firstQuint)Combination of Cryosurgery and NK Immunotherapy for Tumors in Transplanted Liver.

 By enrolling patients with tumors in transplanted liver adapted to enrolled criteria, this study will document for the first time the safety and the short and long term efficacy of the combined therapy using cryosurgery and NK cells.

 The safety will be evaluated by statistics of adverse reactions.

 The efficacy will be evaluated according to local relief degree, progress free survival (PFS) and overall survival (OS).

